The paper proposes algorithms for pattern discovery in event streams, which is a common problem in data management and analysis. The paper also discusses the inherent combinatorial explosion in frequent partial order mining, which is a common problem in data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB (data management), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also proposes a new interestingness measure for partial order episodes, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and similarity measures (cs.SI).
